

Bulgaria expects to expand exchanges and cooperation with China and hopes for more Chinese investment, visiting Bulgarian Prime Minister Sergei Stanishev said during a tour of Shanghai.

Stanishev said in a meeting with Han Zheng, acting party chief and Mayor of Shanghai, that his major missions included looking for new approaches to cement trade cooperation and increasing mutual investment.

Stanishev also gave a speech on EU Enlargement and Bulgaria's Contribution to the EU at the prestigious Fudan University.

The Prime Minister said he expected Bulgaria to contribute to the security and stability of southeast Europe after its accession to the European Union.

Stanishev arrived in Beijing on Sunday where he held talks with Chinese Premier Wen Jiabao, and met with China's top legislator Wu Bangguo and Vice President Zeng Qinghong.

Both sides agreed to take active measures to enhance trade cooperation.

